# .bobignore — files IBM Bob must NOT read, write, or parse.
# Same glob syntax as .gitignore. Kept in sync with the secret-bearing entries
# of .gitignore. Rationale: BobShell sessions are exported to the PUBLIC repo
# (bob/sessions/), so any secret Bob reads could be published.
#
# NOTE: this is a Bob-tool guardrail, not a sandbox. Two things still leak:
#   1. @mentioning a file in a Bob prompt BYPASSES .bobignore — never @ a secret.
#   2. Typing a secret as a BobShell command can still be captured.
# Primary safeguard for the DB password stays the PG* env vars set in your own
# terminal (see infra/supabase/README.md). Restart Bob Shell after editing this.

# ─── Environment / secrets ───
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
.envrc
.streamlit/secrets.toml

# ─── Authorship Passport signing keys (private) ───
keys/
*.pem
*.key
!docs/examples/*.pem.example

# ─── Local data / caches (not secret, but noise) ───
data/
